  "prompt": "What is your horror story at NIT?",
  "response": "Ah, the infamous \"NIT horror story\" trope! While I don\u2019t have personal experiences, I can certainly craft a chilling tale based on the eerie and mysterious vibes often associated with National Institutes of Technology (NITs) campuses. Here's one for you:\n\n---\n\n**The Ghost of the Abandoned Lab**\n\nAt one of the older NITs, nestled deep within the campus, there was an abandoned lab building that had been sealed off for decades. No one knew exactly why it was shut down, but rumors swirled about a tragic incident involving a bright but eccentric professor who vanished one stormy night, leaving behind only his unfinished research.\n\nStudents dared each other to enter the building, but few ever did. Those who tried claimed to hear faint whispers echoing through the halls, as if the walls themselves were reciting complex equations. Some even reported seeing shadowy figures hunched over long-forgotten lab equipment.\n\nOne fateful night, a group of final-year students decided to break into the lab for a dare. Armed with flashlights and nerves of steel, they ventured inside. The air was thick with the smell of rust and decay. As they explored deeper, they stumbled upon a room filled with dusty notebooks and broken glassware. One of the students, curious, picked up a journal and began to read.\n\nIt was the professor\u2019s final notebook. The entries grew increasingly frantic, detailing experiments that defied the laws of physics. The last entry read: *\"I have unlocked the threshold between dimensions, but it has consumed me. If you are reading this, do not repeat my mistakes. They will haunt you too.\"*\n\nSuddenly, the lights in the room flickered, and the temperature plummeted. The students turned to leave, but the door slammed shut. From the shadows emerged a translucent figure\u2014the professor, his eyes hollow and expression tormented. He whispered, *\"Do you want to see what I discovered?\"*\n\nPanicked, the students scrambled to escape. One by one, they found themselves trapped, reliving the professor\u2019s experiments in their minds, their screams muffled by the eerie silence of the lab. The next morning, they were found unconscious outside the building, with no memory of what had happened.\n\nTo this day, the lab remains sealed, but students claim to hear whispers late at night, and some swear they\u2019ve seen the professor\u2019s ghost pacing the corridors, forever trapped between dimensions.\n\n---\n\nSo, what do you think? Would you dare to explore an abandoned lab at your NIT? \ud83d\udc7b",
